The paper deals with private information retrieval protocols, which are commonly studied in the computer security (cs.CR) and information theory (cs.IT) communities. The paper also discusses encoding techniques for reducing storage overhead, which is a topic of interest in the database (cs.DB) and distributed systems (cs.DS) communities. Finally, the paper presents a generalization for resisting collusions of servers, which is a problem studied in the context of distributed computing (cs.DC) and cryptography (cs.CC).
